## 🔑 Anatomy and Cytoarchitecture

### Subdivisions
| Division | Location | Primary Connections |
|----------|---------|-------------------|
| Lateral EC (LEC) | Anterolateral | Receives sensory/object information ("what" pathway — perirhinal cortex, temporal cortex) |
| Medial EC (MEC) | Posteromedial | Receives spatial/contextual information (postrhinal/parahippocampal cortex, retrosplenial cortex) |

### Cortical Layers
| Layer | Cell Types | Key Feature |
|-------|-----------|------------|
| I | Axons, few cells | Molecular layer |
| II | **Island cells** (stellate/pyramidal) | Projects via **perforant path → dentate gyrus** (main hippocampal input) |
| III | Pyramidal cells | Projects to **CA1 and subiculum** (direct temporoammonic path) |
| IV | Absent (unlike neocortex) | "Lamina dissecans" — cell-sparse zone |
| V | Large pyramidal cells | Receives hippocampal output (from CA1/subiculum) |
| VI | Mixed | Projects back to neocortex |

