## 🏥 Clinical Significance

| Condition | EC Involvement | Features |
|-----------|---------------|---------|
| **Alzheimer's disease** | **First site of tau pathology** (Braak stage I-II) | Earliest symptom = episodic memory loss (EC → hippocampal disconnection); EC volume loss on MRI predicts conversion from MCI to AD |
| **Temporal lobe epilepsy** | EC within seizure network; often involved in TLE | Contributes to ictal spread; EC stimulation can trigger déjà vu; EC sclerosis in mesial TLE |
| **Semantic dementia** | Perirhinal > EC (anterior temporal lobe) | Semantic memory loss; EC relatively spared until late |
| **Transient global amnesia** | Possible EC + CA1 involvement | Restricted DWI signal in EC/hippocampus during TGA attacks |
| **Schizophrenia** | EC layer II stellate cells reduced | Disrupted EC→hippocampus connectivity; may underlie formal thought disorder |
| **COVID-19 / post-COVID** | Possible EC vulnerability (ACE2 expression) | Memory complaints; EC atrophy reported in some post-COVID studies |

